{# Try This Section #}
<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="try-this-discovery-prompts">Try this: discovery prompts</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Explore your generated council and notice how the AI has customised everything. Use these prompts to discover the details:
</p>

{# Discovery Prompt 1 #}
<div class="ndx-discovery-card">
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__header">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Spot the theme in service pages</h3>
    <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Beginner</span>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__body">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Navigate to the <strong>Waste & Recycling</strong> service page and read the content carefully.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      <strong>What to look for:</strong> References to your council's theme. Coastal councils mention beach clean-ups and harbour area collections. Industrial heritage councils reference former industrial sites. Market towns mention local businesses.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

{# Discovery Prompt 2 #}
<div class="ndx-discovery-card">
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__header">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Find regional references</h3>
    <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Beginner</span>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__body">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Go to the <strong>Planning Applications</strong> guide and look for mentions of local architectural styles.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      <strong>What to look for:</strong> Regional building references. Northern councils might mention stone buildings and slate roofs. Southern councils could reference chalk, flint, or thatch. Conservation area mentions will reflect the region's character.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

{# Discovery Prompt 3 #}
<div class="ndx-discovery-card">
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__header">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Compare hero images across sections</h3>
    <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--green">Intermediate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__body">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Visit three different service page landing sections and compare the hero images at the top of each.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      <strong>What to look for:</strong> Consistent visual theme across all images. Coastal councils show sea views and harbours. Rural councils show countryside and villages. Urban councils show town centres and high streets.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

{# Discovery Prompt 4 #}
<div class="ndx-discovery-card">
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__header">
    <h3 class="govuk-heading-s govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">Notice councillor diversity</h3>
    <span class="govuk-tag govuk-tag--blue">Beginner</span>
  </div>
  <div class="ndx-discovery-card__body">
    <p class="govuk-body">
      Navigate to the <strong>Council and Democracy</strong> section and find the councillor directory.
    </p>
    <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
      <strong>What to look for:</strong> AI-generated headshots representing different ages, genders, and backgrounds. The councillors are fictional but realistic, typical of UK local council cabinets.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

{# Technical Section #}
<h2 class="govuk-heading-l" id="for-technical-readers">For technical readers</h2>

<p class="govuk-body">
  If you're evaluating the technical architecture or want to understand how generation works under the hood:
</p>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Generation command</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Council generation is triggered by a Drush command during deployment:
</p>

<div class="ndx-code-block">
  <code>drush localgov:generate-council</code>
</div>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Options include <code>--dry-run</code> for preview and <code>--skip-images</code> for faster testing.
</p>

